    <h1 style="font-family: Shruti; margin-left: 40px;"><small><span
          style="color: rgb(0, 0, 153);">OPAL: Opportunistic Alignment
          of Advertisement Delivery with Basestation Overloads</span></small></h1>
    <div style="margin-left: 40px;"><span style="font-family:
        Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"></span><span style="font-family:
        Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">This work is
        motivated by two observations: (1) Cellular network operators
        are
        actively exploring advertisement delivery as a new means </span><span
        style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"></span><span
        style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">of revenue
        generation an</span><span style="font-family:
        Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"></span><span style="font-family:
        Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">d</span><span style="font-family:
        Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"> </span><span style="font-family:
        Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><img style=" width: 411px; height:
          300px;" alt="Picture Not Loading" src="img/opal.png"
          align="right" hspace="50"></span><br>
      <span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">&nbsp;(2)
        Cellular networks perceive intermittent overloads at
        different times of the day. Bringing the two observations, <span
          style="font-family: Comic Sans MS;">OPAL</span> is a
        novel system that opportunistically aligns <br>
        advertisement delivery with
        basestation overload. To achieve the alignment systematically, </span><span
        style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span
          style="font-family: Comic Sans MS;">OPAL</span></span><span
        style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">
        builds on an </span><span style="font-family:
        Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"></span><span style="font-family:
        Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">analytica</span><span
        style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"></span><span
        style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">l framework for
        tunable unavailability of network
        <br>
        service to users during overload. At the same time, if the
        network is
        not overloaded enough during a certain p</span><span
        style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"></span><span
        style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">eriod, </span><span
        style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span
          style="font-family: Comic Sans MS;">OPAL</span></span><span
        style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"> schedules
        enough
        advertisements to satisfy <br>
        the advertisement delivery contracts.</span><span
        style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"></span><br>
      <span style="font-family: helvetica,arial,sans-serif;"></span><br>
      <span style="font-family: helvetica,arial,sans-serif;">
      </span><a style=" color: rgb(51, 51, 255);" href="PAPERS/OPAL.pdf">Conference
        [ACM MobiSys 2011]</a><a style=" color: rgb(51, 51, 255);"
        href="PAPERS/OPAL.pdf"><span style="color: rgb(51, 51, 255);"></span></a><br>
      <span style="font-family: helvetica,arial,sans-serif;"></span><br>
      <br>
      <br>
      <br>
      <br>
      <br>
      <br>
      <br>
      <span style="font-family: helvetica,arial,sans-serif;">
        The following demos show the efficacy of </span><span
        style="font-family: helvetica,arial,sans-serif;"><span
          style="font-family: Comic Sans MS;">OPAL</span></span><span
        style="font-family: helvetica,arial,sans-serif;"> on a WiMAX
        testbed.</span><br>
    </div>
    <span style="font-family: helvetica,arial,sans-serif;"></span> <span
      style="font-family: helvetica,arial,sans-serif;"> </span>
